** About us **

AAMC are Australia’s leading motor accident management and assessing
specialist. We have been delivering services to meet the individual needs of
our clients for over 20 years.

Our people are our greatest asset. We are committed to recruiting and
retaining a talented and diverse pool of extraordinary people. We value their
experience and encourage the informal sharing of knowledge day-to-day.
Formally, we provide a range of development opportunities to take the skills
of our team from good to great.

** The Role **

This role is an excellent opportunity for a tech-savvy individual with a
passion for solution design and development in the Azure environment to use
their skills to deliver value for the business.

As an Azure Developer, you will play an important role implementing new and
supporting existing solutions. You will ensure secure-by-design principles are
followed, technical specifications are documented for approval and solutions
are robust and maintainable. You will also be responsible for working with our
various suppliers’ if the solution requires external expertise.

In this role you will receive guidance to develop your Enterprise Architecture
skills and to learn the technologies required of the role.

You will be operating within a small team who predominantly follow the Agile
methodology. You will have direct access to stakeholders at all levels to
ensure solutions are produced that meet the business need.

Experience with RESTful API development is advantageous.

** Primary Purpose **

The core functions of your role will be to assist in the solution design and
implementation processes. You will also assist in parts of the requirement
gathering process where it will add value from a technical perspective. The
duties of the role include, but are not limited to, the following:  

  * Use requirements and stakeholder engagement to help design solutions that are fit for purpose, 
  * Where ideal for internal development, build the solution in an automated and repeatable way, with an appropriate level of developer, unit and user testing, 
  * Reduce rework by challenging ideas to ensure that solution designs meet the business need or address a root cause, 
  * Clearly document solutions, including technical details and security requirements, 
  * Implement robust solutions with adequate monitoring and alerting, 
  * Ensure reporting can be derived from the solution to support business decisions, 
  * Where an existing solution fails, fix the issue immediately, but also identify the root cause and propose a solution to prevent future incidents, 
  * Supply data and insights to support the analysis of ROI post-implementation to validate our decision-making processes, 
  * Support the business at all levels to help address problems or improve efficiencies using your technical skillset. 

You will use the following tools to build technical solutions:

  * Azure resources such as: 
  * Functions (with Python) 
  * Service Bus 
  * Logic Apps 
  * Key Vault 
  * Storage accounts (Blob and SFTP) 
  * Cosmos Db 
  * Azure Data Explorer 
  * API Management 
  * Programming tools used: 
  * Docker 
  * GitHub 
  * GitHub Actions (with Terraform) 
  * VS Code 
  * JIRA and Confluence 

** About You **

  * You are energetic, motivated, and love to solve problems, 
  * You have at least 2 years previous experience in a similar role, or have performed these duties in a different role, 
  * Experience using Azure resources, ideally at a minimum; Azure Functions, Service Bus, Logic Apps, 
  * Medium to advanced knowledge of Python, 
  * Be able to, and interested in, learning new technologies and applying that knowledge to building solutions, 
  * An ability to multi-task, juggle competing deadlines whilst projecting a calm and confident attitude, 
  * Demonstrated ability to problem solve and think originally, 
  * Exceptional interpersonal skills, including the ability to participate and collaborate in individual and team settings, 
  * The ability to communicate clearly and concisely to explain difficult or complex concepts to both technical experts as well as laypeople, 
  * General Insurance knowledge of terminology and processes is highly desirable. 

** What’s in it for You? **

As well as a fun, energetic work environment, AAMC can offer:

  * A competitive salary + super + internet allowance + all equipment provided 
  * 100% working from your home office – great work/life balance 
  * Being part of a supportive and friendly culture 
  * Employee Assistance Program 

** How to Apply **

Applications in the form of a resume, ** plus cover letter ** , may be
submitted by clicking ‘Apply Now’.

The successful applicant will be required to obtain a National Australian
Police check.

Applicants for this position, must have the right to work and live in this
location.

